#. <section class="sutta" id="sn10.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn10.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga"
msgstr "1. With Indaka"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn10.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Sudattasutta"
msgstr "8. With Sudatta"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.211"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.456"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati sītavane."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha in the Cool Grove."

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati rājagahaṃ anuppatto hoti "
"kenacideva karaṇīyena."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the householder Anāthapiṇḍika had arrived at Rājagaha on "
"some business."

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.3"
msgid "Assosi kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati:"
msgstr "He heard"

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.4"
msgid "“buddho kira loke uppanno”ti."
msgstr "a rumor that a Buddha had arisen in the world."

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.5"
msgid ""
"Tāvadeva ca pana bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamitukāmo hoti. Athassa "
"anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Right away he wanted to go and see the Buddha, but he thought:"

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.6"
msgid "“akālo kho ajja bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr "“It’s too late to go and see the Buddha today."

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.7"
msgid ""
"Sve dānāhaṃ kālena bhagavantaṃ dassanāya gamissāmī”ti buddhagatāya satiyā "
"nipajji."
msgstr "I’ll go and see him tomorrow.” He went to bed thinking of the Buddha."

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.8"
msgid "Rattiyā sudaṃ tikkhattuṃ vuṭṭhāsi pabhātanti maññamāno."
msgstr "During the night he got up three times thinking it was morning."

#. VAR: sivathikadvāraṃ → sīvathikadvāraṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn10.8:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena sivathikadvāraṃ tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "Then he approached the Sivaka Gate,"

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.10"
msgid "Amanussā dvāraṃ vivariṃsu."
msgstr "and non-human beings opened it for him."

msgctxt "sn10.8:1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa nagaramhā nikkhamantassa āloko "
"antaradhāyi, andhakāro pāturahosi, bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso udapādi, "
"tatova puna nivattitukāmo ahosi."
msgstr ""
"But as he was leaving the city, light vanished and darkness appeared to him. "
"He felt fear, terror, and goosebumps, and wanted to turn back."

#. VAR: sivako → sīvako (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn10.8:1.12"
msgid "Atha kho sivako yakkho antarahito saddamanussāvesi:"
msgstr "Then the invisible spirit Sivaka called out:"

# BB follows comm in expanding this to 100,000, but the Chinese parallels at SA 592 and SA2 186 prefer the more modest and literal figure of 100.
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc837"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.1"
msgid "“Sataṃ hatthī sataṃ assā,"
msgstr "“A hundred elephants, a hundred horses,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.2"
msgid "Sataṃ assatarīrathā;"
msgstr "a hundred mule-drawn chariots,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.3"
msgid "Sataṃ kaññāsahassāni,"
msgstr "a hundred thousand maidens"

# āmukka is a variant of āmutta.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.4"
msgid "Āmukkamaṇikuṇḍalā;"
msgstr "bedecked with jewels and earrings:"

# BB’s “step” for padavitihara is incorrect, it is a special term denoting a “great stride forward” for which “stride” alone is barely adequate. He has adopted “stride” in AN.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.5"
msgid "Ekassa padavītihārassa,"
msgstr "these are not worth a sixteenth part"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:2.6"
msgid "Kalaṃ nāgghanti soḷasiṃ."
msgstr "of a single forward stride!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc838"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:3.1"
msgid "Abhikkama gahapati,"
msgstr "Forward, householder!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:3.2"
msgid "abhikkama gahapati;"
msgstr "Forward, householder!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:3.3"
msgid "Abhikkamanaṃ te seyyo,"
msgstr "Going forward is better for you,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:3.4"
msgid "no paṭikkamanan”ti."
msgstr "not turning back!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa andhakāro antaradhāyi, āloko "
"pāturahosi, yaṃ ahosi bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso, so paṭippassambhi."
msgstr ""
"Then darkness vanished and light appeared to Anāthapiṇḍika. His fear, "
"terror, and goosebumps settled down."

msgctxt "sn10.8:4.2"
msgid ""
"Dutiyampi kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa āloko antaradhāyi, andhakāro "
"pāturahosi, bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso udapādi, tatova puna "
"nivattitukāmo ahosi."
msgstr "But for a second time, light vanished and darkness appeared to him. …"

msgctxt "sn10.8:4.3"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho sivako yakkho antarahito saddamanussāvesi:"
msgstr "For a second time the invisible spirit Sivaka called out …"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc839"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:5.1"
msgid "“Sataṃ hatthī sataṃ assā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:5.2"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:5.3"
msgid "Kalaṃ nāgghanti soḷasiṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.457"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:6.1"
msgid "Abhikkama gahapati,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:6.2"
msgid "abhikkama gahapati;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:6.3"
msgid "Abhikkamanaṃ te seyyo,"
msgstr "“… Going forward is better for you,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:6.4"
msgid "no paṭikkamanan”ti."
msgstr "not turning back!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.212"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa andhakāro antaradhāyi, āloko "
"pāturahosi, yaṃ ahosi bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso, so paṭippassambhi."
msgstr ""
"Then darkness vanished and light appeared to Anāthapiṇḍika. His fear, "
"terror, and goosebumps settled down."

msgctxt "sn10.8:7.2"
msgid ""
"Tatiyampi kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa āloko antaradhāyi, andhakāro "
"pāturahosi, bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso udapādi, tatova puna "
"nivattitukāmo ahosi."
msgstr "But for a third time, light vanished and darkness appeared to him. …"

msgctxt "sn10.8:7.3"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho sivako yakkho antarahito saddamanussāvesi:"
msgstr "For a third time the invisible spirit Sivaka called out …"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:8.1"
msgid "“Sataṃ hatthī sataṃ assā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:8.2"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:8.3"
msgid "Kalaṃ nāgghanti soḷasiṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:9.1"
msgid "Abhikkama gahapati,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:9.2"
msgid "abhikkama gahapati;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:9.3"
msgid "Abhikkamanaṃ te seyyo,"
msgstr "“… Going forward is better for you,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:9.4"
msgid "no paṭikkamanan”ti."
msgstr "not turning back!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:10.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa andhakāro antaradhāyi, āloko "
"pāturahosi, yaṃ ahosi bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃso, so paṭippassambhi."
msgstr ""
"Then darkness vanished and light appeared to Anāthapiṇḍika. His fear, "
"terror, and goosebumps settled down."

msgctxt "sn10.8:10.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena sītavanaṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went to the Cool Grove and approached the "
"Buddha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.458"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:11.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya abbhokāse "
"caṅkamati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Buddha had risen at the crack of dawn and was walking "
"meditation in the open."

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.2"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr "He saw Anāthapiṇḍika coming off in the distance."

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.3"
msgid "Disvāna caṅkamā orohitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"So he stepped down from the walking path, sat down on the seat spread out,"

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.4"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to Anāthapiṇḍika:"

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.5"
msgid "“ehi, sudattā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Sudatta.”"

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati, nāmena maṃ bhagavā ālapatīti, haṭṭho udaggo "
"tattheva bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Anāthapiṇḍika thought: “The Buddha calls my name!” Smiling and joyful, "
"he bowed with his head to the Buddha’s feet and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn10.8:11.7"
msgid "“kacci, bhante, bhagavā sukhamasayitthā”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, I trust the Buddha slept well?”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc840"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:12.1"
msgid "“Sabbadā ve sukhaṃ seti,"
msgstr "“A brahmin who is fully extinguished"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:12.2"
msgid "brāhmaṇo parinibbuto;"
msgstr "always sleeps well."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:12.3"
msgid "Yo na limpati kāmesu,"
msgstr "Sensual pleasures slide off them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:12.4"
msgid "sītibhūto nirūpadhi."
msgstr "they’re cooled, free of attachments."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc841"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.8:13.1"
msgid "Sabbā āsattiyo chetvā,"
msgstr "Since they’ve cut off all clinging,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:13.2"
msgid "vineyya hadaye daraṃ;"
msgstr "and removed the stress from the heart,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.8:13.3"
msgid "Upasanto sukhaṃ seti,"
msgstr "the peaceful sleep well,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: cetasā”ti → cetasoti (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn10.8:13.4"
msgid "santiṃ pappuyya cetasā”ti."
msgstr "abiding in peace of mind.”"
